      "active route is index.html -> src/runtime.mjs -> src/game.js -> dino scaffold -> src/runtime-terrain-v6.mjs, not the older index.html -> src/runtime.mjs -> src/runtime-terrain-v6.mjs route",
      "runtime motion.speed = 15 vs runner-tuning.json motion.baseForwardSpeed = 13.5",
      "runtime motion.maxSpeed = 25 vs runner-tuning.json motion.maxForwardSpeed = 24",
      "runtime motion.boostSpeed = 31 vs runner-tuning.json motion.boostForwardSpeed = 29",
      "runtime motion.turnRate = 2.55 vs runner-tuning.json motion.turnRate = 2.45",
      "runtime terrain.chunkSize = 46 vs runner-tuning.json terrain.chunkSize = 44",
      "runtime terrain.segments = 24 vs runner-tuning.json terrain.chunkSegments = 20",
      "runtime terrain.seed = 238991 vs runner-tuning.json terrain.seed = prehistoric-rush-infinite-terrain-v1",
      "game-scenes.json uses run-over as canonical loss scene while scenes/game.json still declares nextOnLoss as fail",
      "runtime win threshold is inline distance > 3600 instead of manifest-owned",
      "runtime spawn counts and clear radius are inline instead of manifest-owned",
      "runtime jump consumption is a raw boolean reset instead of an ActionFrame/RunnerStepResult fact",
      "runtime hazard, pickup, and win outcomes mutate app.scene or runner state without durable ContactEvent records",
      "runtime host exposes getState only; no diagnostics, dispatch, replay journal, source snapshot, dino domain bridge report, or smoke runner exists yet"
    ],
    "requiredFixes": [
      "treat src/game.js as the canonical composition entry after src/runtime.mjs",
      "bridge live runner movement into runner.moved events",
      "surface dino form, pose, and material domain snapshots in diagnostics",
      "load manifests before runtime setup",
      "emit ManifestLoadStatus and ManifestDriftReport before changing visible behavior",
      "normalize nextOnLoss from fail to run-over or keep fail as explicit compatibility alias only",
      "make inline tuning fallback-only",
      "surface loaded config, fallback status, alias status, drift status, source snapshot, dino domain bridge status, and fixture status in PrehistoricRushHost.getDiagnostics()",
      "route button, keyboard, and future touch input through ActionFrame records",
      "separate accepted action journal from rejected input diagnostics",
      "route start, retry, menu, run-over, win, and run-again through SceneDispatchResult records",
      "route movement tick, hazard hit, shard pickup, and distance goal through RunnerStepResult, RunnerEvent, and ContactEvent records",
      "add replayable scripted fixture coverage before terrain/render/raptor/camera/flock/Rapier extraction",
      "emit RunMovementPromotionReport after fixture parity defines the shared run-movement-kit boundary"
